{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove biodiversity net gain mandate from the Environment Bill",
        "additional_details": "You surely cannot re-establish an environment, which has taken tens of thousands of years to develop, in a period of thirty years.\r\n\r\nThe biodiversity net gain mandate in the Environment Bill could do more damage to our biodiversity than good. I worry it puts far too much power in the hands of developers and not enough in the hands of the public.",
        "background": "The Government must remove the biodiversity net gain requirement from the Environment Bill, as this merely attempts to \u2018incentivise\u2019 developers to avoid the \u2018most biodiverse\u2019 sites, meaning they could build on already well-established biodiverse land in the absence of stronger protections. ",
